The paper deals with the problem of learning a latent variable model from a stream of data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on single topic models, which are commonly used in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves analyzing the performance of the algorithm in both synthetic and real-world experiments, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
